Convert Data

# convert data frames to wide format for analyses first uses psmelt - then
# reshape data - then keeps all OTUs that don't contain the ':' symbol =>
# gets diagnostic OTUs only.
data_convert <- function(data, df, taxa.level, filter_value = 1e-04) {
    
    # Melt data from phyloseq package
    dat <- psmelt(data)
    
    # Convert data into usable form
    dat <- dat %>% filter(Abundance > 0) %>% group_by(Sample) %>% mutate(rank.abund = sum(Abundance)) %>% 
        mutate(rel_ab = Abundance/rank.abund) %>% mutate(bact_pres = ifelse(rel_ab > 
        0, 1, 0)) %>% group_by(OTU) %>% mutate(rank.abund.taxa = sum(Abundance)) %>% 
        mutate(ra.taxa = Abundance/rank.abund.taxa) %>% filter(ra.taxa > filter_value)
    
    dat$OTU <- as.factor(dat$OTU)
    dat$Sample <- as.factor(dat$Sample)
    dat$Gender <- as.factor(dat$Gender)
    
    dat <- as.data.frame(dat[, c("OTU", "Sample", "Age", "Gender", "BMI", "Status", 
        "BMI_Cat", "bact_pres")])
    
    # convert data into 'wide' format for the random forest analysis
    dat <- reshape(dat, idvar = "Sample", timevar = "OTU", v.names = "bact_pres", 
        direction = "wide")
    
    # Recode status
    dat$CRC <- ifelse(dat$Status == "CRC", 1, 0)
    
    # ONLY need the following for the otu level datasets from 16S sequencing
    # This part of the code subsets to only the single identified otus, i.e.
    # eliminates otus that had multiple guesses.  if(taxa.level == 'otu'){ if(df
    # == 'baxter' | df =='zackular' | df == 'zeller.Stool' | df ==
    # 'zeller.Tissue'){ dat <- dat[,-grep(':', colnames(dat))] } }
    
    
    # replace NAs with 0, which makes sense in this case because the conversion
    # from long to wide creates NA when the abundance is actually just 0.
    dat[is.na(dat)] <- 0
    return(dat)
}

Logistic Regression Model

The logistic regression model aims to predict the probability of the outcome variable being a 1. So, in this case, 1 is the the identifer we use to denote an individual has CRC and 0 represents a non-CRC individual. Therefore, let Y = 1 if an individual has CRC or Y = 0 otherwise. We are only interesting in obese individuals as well, so the dataset will be subsetted to only these individuals.

\[ \log \frac{Pr(Y_i = 1)}{1 - Pr(Y_i = 1)} = a_j\]

where the logit (a) varies based on the study being analyzed.

Functional Form

logistic_regression <- function(data, bact) {
    out <- numeric(6)
    check <- tryCatch(data[, bact], error = function(cond) return(NA))
    
    if (is.na(check[1]) == F) {
        data <- data[, c("CRC", bact, "BMI", "Age", "Gender")]  #'BMI', 'Age', 'Gender'
        data$c.BMI <- data$BMI - mean(data$BMI)
        data$c.Age <- data$Age - mean(data$Age)
        data$female <- ifelse(data$Gender == "female", 1, 0)
        colnames(data) <- c("CRC", "Bact", "BMI", "Age", "Gender", "c.BMI", 
            "c.Age", "female")  #'BMI', 'Age'
        beta <- numeric(3)
        OR <- numeric(3)
        
        # 1) estimate regression CRC on BMI
        fit1 <- glm(CRC ~ Bact + female + c.BMI + c.Age, data = data, family = "binomial")
        
        beta <- cbind(coef(fit1), confint(fit1))[2, ]
        OR <- exp(cbind(coef(fit1), confint(fit1)))[2, ]
        
        
        out <- c(beta, OR)
    } else {
        # Run the following if the first check fails...  means that the bacteria was
        # not in data
        out <- rep(NA, 6)
    }
    return(out)
}

Run Analyses

# Run mediation analyses
logit_results <- matrix(ncol = 8)

i <- 1
# loop through datasets
for (df in datasets) {
    # extract data from saved object
    data <- wk.data[[df]]
    bact.i <- bacterialist[[df]]
    # initialize blank mediation table for output
    logit_table <- matrix(ncol = 6, nrow = length(bact.i))
    
    # Loop through bacteria
    for (i in 1:length(bact.i)) {
        logit_table[i, ] <- logistic_regression(data, bact.i[i])
    }
    
    # Do some naming for my sanity
    colnames(logit_table) <- c("Beta", "LL_Beta", "UL_Beta", "OR", "LL_OR", 
        "UL_OR")
    
    Study <- rep(df, length(bact.i))
    Bacteria <- substr(bact.i, 11, nchar(bact.i))
    res <- cbind(Study, Bacteria, round(logit_table, 5))
    # update mediation results
    logit_results <- rbind(logit_results, res)
}

Compiling Results

logits <- as.data.frame(logit_results)
logits$OR <- as.numeric(logits$OR)
logits$OR <- ifelse(logits$OR < 0.01, 0.01, logits$OR)
logits$OR <- ifelse(logits$OR > 100, 100, logits$OR)

logits$LL_OR <- as.numeric(logits$LL_OR)
logits$LL_OR <- ifelse(logits$LL_OR < 0.01, 0.01, logits$LL_OR)
logits$LL_OR <- ifelse(is.na(logits$LL_OR) == T, 0.01, logits$LL_OR)

logits$UL_OR <- as.numeric(logits$UL_OR)
logits$UL_OR <- ifelse(logits$UL_OR > 100, 100, logits$UL_OR)
logits$UL_OR <- ifelse(is.na(logits$UL_OR) == T, 100, logits$UL_OR)

logits$OR <- log2(as.numeric(logits$OR))
logits$LL_OR <- log2(as.numeric(logits$LL_OR))
logits$UL_OR <- log2(as.numeric(logits$UL_OR))
